      • getDBTag

        protected java.lang.String getDBTag()
        Description copied from class: FilterReader
        Get the tag used to create the connection for this query from a DatabaseService. Normally this just queries the repository for the main table in the query (as this table HAS to take part) and relies on the query failing if there is an illegal join. Any more advanced checking should really be done when constructing the filter as this is where there is a chance to recover from the error.
